1) no need for outline or bibliography
	A) type out the speech and turn it in, 2-6 minute speech

2) creativity and delivery is most important

3) types of speech
	A) speech of introduction
		I) be brief
		II) be accurate
		III) adapt to occasion
		IV) build snese of anticipation
	B) speech of presentation
		I) giving a gift or an award
		II) critertia
			a) why did they recieve the award?
	C) acceptancce speech
		I) thank the organization that gave you the award
	D) commemoration
		I) speech paying tribute to group or person
		II) eulogy, celebration
			a) to a group or person

